                                                    </li>
                                                    <li>Insurance of producers or their primary produce</li>
                                                    <li>Promoting techniques of mutuality and mutual assistance</li>
                                                    <li>
                                                        Welfare measures or facilities for the benefit of Members as may be decided by the
                                                        Board
                                                    </li>
                                                    <li>
                                                        Any other activity, ancillary or incidental to any of the activities referred to in
                                                        above clauses which may promote the principles of mutuality and mutual assistance
                                                        amongst the Members in any other manner
                                                    </li>
                                                    <li>
                                                        Financing of procurement, processing, marketing or other activities specified in above
                                                        clauses which include extending credit facilities or any other financial services to its
                                                        members
                                                    </li>
                                                </ul>
                                            </div>

